Pointers

Memory - hex
	- format is 0x
	- base 16
	- 0-9 a-f
	- example
		- 0xF = 15
		- 0x0 = 0
		- 0xFF = 255

Memory - structure
	- like an array
	- the address can be accessed using the '&' symbol

Memory - Size
	- always points to the first place on memory, regardless of the size.
	- Size depends on operating system

Pointer - Variables
	- syntax = int* pointer 
	- int* = pointer value
	- *pointer makes pointer become a pointer value
	- arrays and pointers are very similar execpt they start out initialized

Pointer - arithmetic
	